metrics_java¶

This module provides a tool for computing metrics (from static analysis) for python source code using Using CK Package @Alvaro 26 Jan 2021

Using CK Package

CK is a java package (jar) which is going to be executed from terminal. It requires the code which is going to be analyzed to be located at physical files. For that reason, the dataset is going to be used to produce some .java files.

Available metrics:

Further info. can be found at the github repository of the project.

  • wmc: Weight Method Class or McCabe's complexity
  • totalMethodsQty:
  • staticMethodsQty
  • publicMethodsQty
  • privateMethodsQty
  • protectedMethodsQty
  • defaultMethodsQty
  • abstractMethodsQty
  • finalMethodsQty
  • synchronizedMethodsQty
  • totalFieldsQty
  • staticFieldsQty
  • publicFieldsQty
  • privateFieldsQty
  • protectedFieldsQty
  • defaultFieldsQty
  • visibleFieldsQty
  • finalFieldsQty
  • synchronizedFieldsQty
  • nosi: Number of static invocations invocations to static methods
  • loc: Lines of code
  • returnQty
  • loopQty
  • comparisonsQty
  • tryCatchQty
  • parenthesizedExpsQty
  • stringLiteralsQty
  • numbersQty: Number literals
  • assignmentsQty
  • mathOperationsQty
  • variablesQty
  • maxNestedBlocksQty: The highest number of blocks nested together.
  • anonymousClassesQty
  • innerClassesQty
  • lambdasQty
  • uniqueWordsQty
  • modifiers

Each record, corresponds to a individual class.

write_dataset_to_files[source]

write_dataset_to_files(df_series, destination_path)

Function to generate .java files.

Params:

df_series: Pandas Series (DataFrame column) with the source code records.¶

destination_path: (str) Absolute path to be used as directory for the generated files.¶

Returns:

Collection of paths for the corresponding java files.

Execute jar file from python and get the output

class JavaAnalyzer[source]

JavaAnalyzer(ck_jar_path)

Class get metrics f

# General parameters for testing

def get_default_params():
    return {
    'ck_jar_path': 'ck_metrics_tool/ck-metrics.jar',
    'search_net_ds_path': '/tf/main/dvc-ds4se/code/searchnet/clean_java.csv',
    'sampling_size': 100,
    'physical_files_path': '/tf/main/nbs/test_data/test_metrics'
}

Testing JavaAnalyzer¶

Explore with some data

params = get_default_params()

java_analyzer = JavaAnalyzer(params['ck_jar_path'])

java_df = pd.read_csv(params['search_net_ds_path'])

samples = java_df.sample(params['sampling_size'])

paths = write_dataset_to_files(samples['code'], params['physical_files_path'])

Generating physical .java files.

java_metrics = java_analyzer.compute_metrics(samples['code'], params['physical_files_path'])
